#WATCH | Fresh tensions are rising in the Middle East after the U.N. paused ship evacuation operations through the Strait of Hormuz following an attack on a vessel near Oman. The move comes after Iran warned ships against using routes not approved by Tehran. 

With nearly 20% of the world’s oil and gas shipments passing through the Strait of Hormuz, the incident has renewed fears of supply disruptions, higher oil prices, and fresh uncertainty over the fragile U.S.-Iran peace talks.

@ShivaniSinghRna reports!

